   "source": [
    "What is XGBoost?\n",
    "\n",
    "XGBoost = eXtreme Gradient Boosting\n",
    "\n",
    "It is an improved version of Gradient Boosting Decision Trees (GBDT).\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of building one huge decision tree, it builds many small trees sequentially.\n",
    "\n",
    "The next tree tries to correct the mistakes made by the previous trees.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Tree 1:\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicts house price = ₹50L\n",
    "\n",
    "Actual:\n",
    "\n",
    "₹60L\n",
    "\n",
    "Error:\n",
    "\n",
    "₹10L\n",
    "\n",
    "Tree 2:\n",
    "\n",
    "Learns this error and tries to reduce it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Tree 3:\n",
    "\n",
    "Further reduces remaining error.\n",
    "\n",
    "Final prediction:\n",
    "\n",
    "Sum of all tree outputs.\n",
    "Why is it so famous?\n",
    "\n",
    "Because it usually gives:\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ High Accuracy\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ Handles Missing Values\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ Works on Large Datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ Feature Importance\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ Regularization (prevents overfitting)\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ Fast Training\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ Parallel Processing\n",
    "\n",
    "Difference from Random Forest\n",
    "\n",
    "Many beginners confuse these.\n",
    "\n",
    "Random Forest\n",
    "Trees are built independently.\n",
    "Final answer = average/voting of all trees.\n",
    "Tree1\n",
    "Tree2\n",
    "Tree3\n",
    "Tree4\n",
    "\n",
    "All trees work separately.\n",
    "\n",
    "XGBoost\n",
    "\n",
    "Trees are built sequentially.\n",
    "\n",
    "Tree1\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Tree2 fixes Tree1 mistakes\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Tree3 fixes Tree2 mistakes\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Tree4 fixes Tree3 mistakes\n",
    "\n",
    "This boosting process usually gives better accuracy."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
