   "source": [
    "Most Important Parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "XGBClassifier(\n",
    "    n_estimators=200,\n",
    "    max_depth=5,\n",
    "    learning_rate=0.1,\n",
    "    subsample=0.8,\n",
    "    colsample_bytree=0.8\n",
    ")\n",
    "n_estimators\n",
    "\n",
    "Number of trees.\n",
    "\n",
    "n_estimators=100\n",
    "\n",
    "More trees → better learning but slower.\n",
    "\n",
    "max_depth\n",
    "\n",
    "Depth of tree.\n",
    "\n",
    "max_depth=5\n",
    "\n",
    "Higher depth can overfit.\n",
    "\n",
    "learning_rate\n",
    "\n",
    "How much each tree contributes.\n",
    "\n",
    "learning_rate=0.1\n",
    "\n",
    "Smaller value:\n",
    "\n",
    "Slower learning\n",
    "Better generalization\n",
    "subsample\n",
    "\n",
    "Uses only a portion of data for each tree.\n",
    "\n",
    "subsample=0.8\n",
    "\n",
    "Helps prevent overfitting.\n",
    "\n",
    "Feature Importance\n",
    "\n",
    "One amazing thing:\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from xgboost import plot_importance\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_importance(model)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "You can see which features matter most.\n",
    "\n",
    "Useful in:\n",
    "\n",
    "Finance\n",
    "Healthcare\n",
    "Marketing\n",
    "Fraud Detection"
   ]
